definition.value: Used to conjugate carboxyl functional groups to primary amines from peptides and proteins and is ideal for covalently binding proteins or peptides to carboxyl containing beads, resins, or nanoparticles.
Used to convert alcohols and amines into carbamates, esters, and ureas.
Used for coupling amines and carboxylates without the insertion of spacer atoms.
Used in conjunction with EDC-HCl (EDAC-HCl) to convert carboxyl groups to NHS esters which react with primary amines.
Used in conjunction with EDC-HCl (EDAC-HCl) to convert carboxyl groups to Sulfo-NHS esters which react with primary amines.

value.value: An isotopically-coded cleavable crosslinker affinity-purifyable with antibodies.

Biotin-aspartate-Rink-glycine cross-linker composed of a biotin affinity handle (B), a pentafluorophenyl (PFP) ester modified aspartate reside (D), a Rink group (R), and a PFP ester modified glycine reside (G).
